<paragraph id="533336B3E449FFF3FF4960B37E9BFEA7" blockId="39.[151,1436,151,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FF4960B37BFFFF51" bold="true" box="[199,466,151,176]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E449FFF3FC8560BD7958FF51" box="[779,885,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FC8560BD7958FF51" box="[779,885,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: acrostichals present; and median volsella at apex of subtriangular projection of inferior volsella. The pupa by: tergite II with stronger shagreen orally; tergite VI with shagreen in anterior 2/3; tergites VII and VIII without shagreen; paratergite VIII with long spines; anal spur of tergite VIII with minute accessory teeth; and conjunctive IV/V with spinules in a single patch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B966538E449FFF3FF4961767E42FE57" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph id="533336B3E449FFF3FF4961767E42FE57" blockId="39.[151,1436,151,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FF4961767B74FE8A" bold="true" box="[199,345,338,363]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Description.</emphasis>
The male was described in detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="371D4B42E449FFF3FC94617679D1FE8A" author="Pinho, L. C. &amp; Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T." box="[794,1020,338,363]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="255 - 264" refId="ref50683" refString="Pinho, L. C., Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) New species and records of Beardius Reiss &amp; Sublette from Brazil (Diptera, Chironomidae). Spixiana, 32, 255 - 264." type="journal article" year="2009">
Pinho 
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FCE96177798EFE8A" box="[871,931,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. The structure considered to be the “median volsella” by 
<bibRefCitation id="371D4B42E449FFF3FE1D61537840FE71" author="Pinho, L. C. &amp; Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T." box="[403,621,375,400]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="255 - 264" refId="ref50683" refString="Pinho, L. C., Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) New species and records of Beardius Reiss &amp; Sublette from Brazil (Diptera, Chironomidae). Spixiana, 32, 255 - 264." type="journal article" year="2009">
Pinho 
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FE50615C7834FE71" box="[478,537,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
must be regarded as a basal subtriangular lobe of the inferior volsella while the 2–3 setae situated on the apex of this projection the wart-like median volsella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B966538E449FFF3FF4961E67EF5FE3A" box="[199,1240,450,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="533336B3E449FFF3FF4961E67EF5FE3A" blockId="39.[151,1436,151,475]" box="[199,1240,450,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FF4961E67B4DFE3A" bold="true" box="[199,352,450,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is recorded from the Amazonas State in 
<collectingCountry id="2B9B7623E449FFF3FC3D61E679DAFE3A" box="[947,1015,450,475]" name="Brazil" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="371D4B42E449FFF3FB8861E67EE1FE3A" author="Pinho, L. C. &amp; Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T." box="[1030,1228,450,475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="255 - 264" refId="ref50683" refString="Pinho, L. C., Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) New species and records of Beardius Reiss &amp; Sublette from Brazil (Diptera, Chironomidae). Spixiana, 32, 255 - 264." type="journal article" year="2009">
Pinho 
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E449FFF3FBDE61E77EA4FE3A" box="[1104,1161,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
